snippet: Winnebago Industries sold more lower-priced motor homes in the fourth quarter, sending its shares down as much as 7 percent to a 16-month low.
abstract: Winnebago Industries reports fourth-quarter net income of $12.9 million, or 48 cents per share, up from $10.6 million, or 38 cents per share, one year earlier; reports that revenue rose nearly 15 percent to $245.9 million.
lead_paragraph: Winnebago Industries sold more lower-priced motor homes in the fourth quarter, sending its shares down as much as 7 percent to a 16-month low.

headline.main: Winnebago Reports 8.4% Drop in Mean Price of Motor Homes
headline.print_headline: Winnebago Reports 8.4%. Drop in Mean Price of Motor Homes
